Dependencies:
sudo apt-get install build-essential libqt4-dev libx11-6 libx11-dev
 
BUILD & INSTALLATION:


Build and install in /usr/local (default prefix):

    mkdir build && cd build
    qmake ..
    make && make install

To install into another prefix use:

    mkdir build && cd build
    qmake PREFIX=/path/to/prefix ..
    make && make install

NOTE:
on some distros you may want to use qmake-qt4 or qmake-qt5 instead of qmake

NOTE2:
non absolute path in PREFIX will be located in .pro's directory and NOT in current working directory, e.g.

    mkdir build && cd build
    qmake PREFIX=install ..
    make && make install

will create an 'install' directory inside your project's root (.pro location),
to install inside your current dir use:

    mkdir build && cd build
    qmake PREFIX=$(pwd)/install ..
    make && make install
